Fantastic copy of a very deep movie.  Thank you for uploading things for ADULTS.  I've noticed that this seeder's uploads usually put the burden on high bandwidth leechers to upload 2-3x before completing.  Maybe that's necessary on TPB, but is very limiting for those who want to give and take voluntarily.

Again, thanks, and here's hoping you'll continue to UL intelligent stuff.  (Any chance of a DVD-R version of Midnight in Paris?)

Many, many thanks for this perfect copy of one of the most important films made in several years.  I believe it will occupy a place in cinema history next to Kubrick's "2001: A Space Odyssey."

For those who care to know, this is a direct DVD rip including the menu.  Audio (English only) is available in 2.0 and 5.1 DD.  Optional subtitles are in English or Spanish.

And for fredfan: be a little more patent.  "Midnight in Paris" is not due out on DVD until sometime in December (I am waiting for it, too).
